## This commit (stage 5/10: calls query engine)
The heart of the CH re-target. _compile_calls_query compiles the mongo
AST once into a closure-per-record predicate mirroring
process_query_to_conditions. Key semantics, all verified against a live
clickhouse server (26.5, clickhouse local) where in doubt:
- JSON_VALUE runs with function_json_value_return_type_allow_complex=1
  (set in clickhouse_trace_server_settings.py:71): objects/arrays come
  back as minified JSON, numbers normalized ('5.0'->'5', '1e3'->'1000'),
  missing/JSON-null -> '', bools 'true'/'false'. _ch_json_value
  implements exactly this; the round-1 assumption (arrays -> '' per CH
  defaults) was WRONG and test_calls_query_filter_contains_in_message_array
  caught it.
- Casts: _to_int64_or_null/_to_float64_or_null/_to_uint8_or_null mirror
  to*OrNull; bool cast is the multiIf chain.
- _ch_compare propagates NULL (None) through comparisons; eq-with-None
  literal compiles to 'lhs is None'.
- Sorts: _ch_sorted_by_terms does two stable passes per term with NULLS
  LAST for both directions; dynamic fields sort by the (exists DESC,
  toFloat64OrNull dir, toString dir) triple.
- status CASE order error -> descendant_error -> running -> success;
  latency_ms NULL while running; trace_name via regexpExtract.
- DATETIME_COLUMN_FIELDS normalize datetime literals for comparisons.
- InvalidFieldError for invalid fields; DISALLOWED_FILTERING_FIELDS
  (storage sizes) raise like CH.
- Multi-value feedback: has()/groupArrayIf/arrayExists ('*' = first
  non-empty, anyIf '' default).
- expand_columns: _compile_expanded_field/_resolve_ref_str_for_filter
  resolve refs for filtering AND sorting.
- _live_queue_ids_for_call is here (not the queues stage) because the
  queue-membership filter in the compile engine is its first use; it only
  reads the raw _annotation_queue_items store initialized in stage 1.
- threads_query_stream: CH aggregation with interpolated quantiles
  (p50/p99) — the closure was hoisted to _interpolated_quantile for
  ruff B023 (closure over loop var).
- project_stats: real tallies incl otel_dump_len; raises the CH
  ValueError when no include flag is set.

